<subSubSection id="189D6519FFD379752ADAFB94FD1CD047" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="50383692FFD379752ADAFB94FD1CD047" blockId="2.[155,794,164,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The few specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD379752BC5FB97FD87D2FC" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[428,589,1145,1167]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspersum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD379752BC5FB97FD87D2FC" box="[428,589,1145,1167]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Solanum aspersum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have usually been annotated as the more common and widely distributed 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD3797528AAFB7BFF10D2BB" authority="Dunal" authorityName="Dunal" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aureum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD3797528AAFB7BFCD3D2D8" box="[707,793,1173,1195]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. aureum</emphasis>
Dunal
</taxonomicName>
, also from Andean Ecuador. 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD37975286BFB5CFD57D2BB" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[514,669,1202,1224]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspersum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD37975286BFB5CFD57D2BB" box="[514,669,1202,1224]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Solanum aspersum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from that species in its simple uniseriate, rather than congesteddendritic pubescence (
<figureCitation id="C8BC2A17FFD379752B1BFB04FE7ED373" box="[370,436,1258,1280]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[155,220,1887,1906]" captionTargetBox="[161,999,961,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-451@1.[155,1006,954,1854]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Solanum aspersum. A) portion of stem, with details of trichomes, B) young bud, C) open flower, D) fruiting inflorescence, E) young fruit. A–C drawn from MacDougal et al. 4251, D–E from Zak 1857A. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0010502.g001" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517440/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig 1A</figureCitation>
), and in the elongate buds that open to deeply stellate flowers (
<figureCitation id="C8BC2A17FFD379752BFAFAE8FE3DD36F" box="[403,503,1286,1308]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[155,220,1887,1906]" captionTargetBox="[161,999,961,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-451@1.[155,1006,954,1854]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Solanum aspersum. A) portion of stem, with details of trichomes, B) young bud, C) open flower, D) fruiting inflorescence, E) young fruit. A–C drawn from MacDougal et al. 4251, D–E from Zak 1857A. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0010502.g001" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517440/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1B, C</figureCitation>
). Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD3797528F9FAE8FD2ED36F" authorityName="Dunal" box="[656,740,1286,1308]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aureum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD3797528F9FAE8FD2ED36F" box="[656,740,1286,1308]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. aureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Azuay province in Ecuador have similarly shiny adaxial leaf surfaces to 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD379752B65FAD0FEBAD327" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[268,368,1342,1364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspersum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD379752B65FAD0FEBAD327" box="[268,368,1342,1364]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. aspersum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but always have the characteristic golden dendritic pubescence of that species rather than the simple pubescence of 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD379752B58FA98FE5DD3FF" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[305,407,1398,1420]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspersum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD379752B58FA98FE5DD3FF" box="[305,407,1398,1420]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. aspersum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD379752855FA98FD6BD3FF" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[572,673,1398,1420]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspersum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD379752855FA98FD6BD3FF" box="[572,673,1398,1420]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. aspersum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are usually more cordate than those of 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD379752BC6FA7CFDCED3D4" authorityName="Dunal" box="[431,516,1426,1447]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aureum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD379752BC6FA7CFDCED3D4" box="[431,516,1426,1447]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. aureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but some populations of 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD379752961FA7CFF1DD3B0" authorityName="Dunal" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aureum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD379752961FA7CFF1DD3B0" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. aureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
approach 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD379752B20FA40FE7AD3B0" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[329,432,1454,1475]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspersum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD379752B20FA40FE7AD3B0" box="[329,432,1454,1475]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. aspersum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in overall leaf morphology at first glance. 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD379752A8FFA24FEB5D3AC" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[230,383,1482,1503]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspersum">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD379752A8FFA24FEB5D3AC" box="[230,383,1482,1503]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Solanum aspersum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a very scattered distribution all along the Andes from northern Colombia to central Ecuador and is likely to be found in more of the intervening parts of the cordilleras, but it is apparently rare and easily overlooked.
</paragraph>
